commit_message:
Select policy when running functional test

Add ability to select a storage policy when running
the functional tests by defining the environment variable
SWIFT_TEST_POLICY.

This patch was first introduced by Janie Richling in
feature/ec: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/166097

commit_message:
Volume manager should set filter_function and goodness_function

If a user defines a filter_function or goodness_function in their cinder.conf
file the scheduler should use that function. This change appends those
functions to volume_stats if the driver has not specified them.

Change-Id: I76f90aa3c1bda7564185d8e130926af7d0827e0e
Closes-Bug: #1458061
(cherry picked from commit cbc708b13982bc11eb4956c9f3f1f96f009dafff)

commit_message:
Fix 'no actual-pathname' NetApp API error

Cinder volume logs sometimes show this error

      NetApp API failed. Reason - 13114:
      No actual-pathname for 10.1.0.9:/vol/whatever

with Kilo code and 7-mode DOT system.

The issue is due to our Cinder driver passing the
entire share to the relevant API instead of just
the export path portion of the share.  This only
happens when the NFS image cache is full, and cached
files need to be removed.

Change-Id: I0c40840dac975dd7fd2c62f1f9c0cd3f8c5c1252
Closes-Bug: #1468884
(cherry picked from commit 6a65422c69bd5f2fc363238b2383b66aab575272)

Pin os-brick to the current release

to the existing release.  We want to release new
versions of os-brick in the near future, but force
that update through CI.

commit_message:
workaround: l3 plugin misses dvr_deletens_if_no_port method

Although dvr_deletens_if_no_port isn't part of l3 interface,
it's a part of dvr l3 plugin because ml2 plugin calls the method on
l3 plugin. It causes following exception when deleting network.

TODO:
This patch only addresses AttributeError exception so that some tempest
tests pass. Later the method needs to be implemented meaningfully
in order to support dvr.

commit_message:
Remove usage of assert_called_once in mocks

This was never a real part of the mock api, but mock was happily mocking
it out and letting the tests pass. The new mock release made this
behaviour break, causing tests to fail on all patches. This patch
replaces instances of assert_called_once with an assert of the mock's
call_count.

Closes-Bug: #1473369
Co-Authored-By: Ian Cordasco <graffatcolmingov@gmail.com>
(cherry picked from commit df0e566f2a144f53df77be29abb1f02ff11cf9be)

Conflicts:
	glance/tests/unit/async/test_taskflow_executor.py

Change-Id: I12ff85a9480d8000b0de54939c3be71458162a40

Heat could not create samples with Ceilometer

Heat could not create samples with Ceilometer, because ceilometer client has
change some key words in CREATION_ATTRIBUTES which is using by create sample.

go: fix expect 100-continue in replicator

Sort of.  I mean it's not ideal, but it's probably better than it was.
We might switch to some non-HTTP protocol for replication later, since
we can design it to better deal with the information flow.

commit_message:
go: adding middleware & routing framework

Add middleware & routing framework for hummingbird

It allows hummingbird to statically chain middlewares to both object & proxy server.
It also adds a routing library written by the patch co-author.

Change-Id: Iaa4d1e8c72caff554a86dbf638077483dfb4ebc7
Co-Authored-By: Michael Barton<mike@weirdlooking.com>

commit_message:
Data model updates for active/standby lb topology

3. Add a role column to the amphora table.
   topology can take values: SINGLE, ACTIVE_STANDBY
   role can take values: STANDALONE, MASTER, or BACKUP.

commit_message:
Use shared shell arguments provided by Session

The cinderclient implemented it's own version of the CLI arguments that
are now provided by keystoneclient's session object. This changeset
converts cinder over to utilizing the shared argument registration.

commit_message:
Remove dict assumption from remotable decorator

The remotable decorator still has code that assumes we can use dict-like
accesses on our objects. This converts it to a setattr.

Change-Id: I45c6e3e9e7bde343a67aa3dfdbb3787b21641cd5
Closes-Bug: #1474952

commit_message:
VM up/down status metrics, other libvirt changes

This change is mostly about adding metrics for VM up/down status,
but also adds some documentation and other minor libvirt-related tweaks:

* Added aggregate metrics to the documentation for VM monitoring
* Removed 'cloud_tier' dimension; it was used by TripleO, and is no longer necessary
* Added host_alive_status for inactive VMs
* Added ping check for active VMs
* Added gathering of private_ip for each instance (necessary for ping checks)
* Added detection of the correct ping command to the libvirt detection plugin
* Placeholder for future libvirt metrics

Change-Id: I02ac24090b5eeb305522dc7d80162d576d263a55

commit_message:
EMC ScaleIO Data Client Shim Libvirt Volume Driver

This specification proposes to add a shim libvirt volume driver for
the support of ScaleIO Data Client (SDC) connected volumes. The
addition of SDC support to libvirt will be leveraged by Nova to
attach/detach volumes provided by EMC ScaleIO. This shim driver
will be based on os-brick.

DocImpact
Implements blueprint emc-sdc-libvirt-volume-driver

Change-Id: Idc7191b4f9af069fb018260d07dc58c67f675351

commit_message:
Use proper status code for partial content

Glance v2 previously handled requests to download the image with Range
headers properly but did not set the correct status code per RFC 7233.
A request like:

    GET /v2/images/image-uuid
    Host: glance-api:9292
    Range: bytes=1024-4098

Should see a response like

    HTTP/1.1 206 Partial Content
    Content-Length: 3074

APIImpact
DocImpact

Closes-bug: 1399851
Depends-On: I76fd3746a2c449e257ea2a19c2dc6118be207eec
Change-Id: Ic741328855e6871e0c567db435bf928b6013a2a0

commit_message:
policy: Dynamic Policies Overlay

Adds to ``oslo.policy`` the capability to overlay
rules in policy file with custom rules received
as a regular Python dict.

This feature will be used by Keystone Middleware
in the context of ``Dynamic Policies``, which
will fetch the custom policy rules from Keystone
server and ask ``oslo.policy`` to do the overlay
processing, i.e write them to the policy file.

Partially-Implements: bp dynamic-policies-delivery

Change-Id: I0b960f999a9e52880450a5c18f7f88119be41566

commit_message:
Retry ipmi commands unless the failure is not retriable

Consider that image deployment is a time-consuming operation, most
ipmi failures worth retrying, even when BMC is temporarily offline.
List keywords of error messages in configuration file, ipmi commands
will be aborted if runtime error messages match keywords, otherwise
will be retried.

Closes-Bug: 1474953
Change-Id: Ib9e8c319070d0a509ea672f34d908afad84a2387

commit_message:
Retry ipmi commands unless the failure is not retriable

Consider that image deployment is a time-consuming operation, most
ipmi failures worth retrying, even when BMC is temporarily offline.
List keywords of error messages in configuration file, ipmi command
will be retried if runtime error message does not match keywords.

subject: Change Dockerfile to use Debian as a base
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-07-16 14:42:44.000000000', 'files': ['Dockerfile'], 'message': "Change Dockerfile to use Debian as a base

Ubuntu licensing does not allow for distributing derivatives of Ubuntu,
including containers based on Ubuntu. We currently publish a CoreOS PXE
image with an IPA container embedded. Basing this container on Ubuntu
appears to violate Ubuntu's license. Let's move to Debian to fix this.

Also remove the python3 purge as python3 doesn't exist in the Debian
base image.

Closes-Bug: #1475325
Change-Id: I051e3123f0cd1e66b5e3bae727559fe31467791b
"}]
commit_message:
Change Dockerfile to use Debian as a base

Ubuntu licensing does not allow for distributing derivatives of Ubuntu,
including containers based on Ubuntu. We currently publish a CoreOS PXE
image with an IPA container embedded. Basing this container on Ubuntu
appears to violate Ubuntu's license. Let's move to Debian to fix this.

Also remove the python3 purge as python3 doesn't exist in the Debian
base image.

Closes-Bug: #1475325
Change-Id: I051e3123f0cd1e66b5e3bae727559fe31467791b

Python 3: Replacing unicode with six.text_type for py3 compatibility

The "unicode" type was renamed to "str" in Python 3.
Use six.text_type to make swiftclient compatible with Python 3.

For more information about changes needed for py3
compatibility, see:
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Python3

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-07-14 17:08:10.000000000', 'files': ['cliff/app.py', 'cliff/tests/test_app.py'], 'message': "Allow subcommands to accept --help when using 'deferred_help'.

This patch changes how cliff handles help for subcommands but only when
'deferred_help' is enabled. Currently cliff consumes --help requests at the top
level. This means `myapp foo --help` and `myapp --help` produce the same output.
To get help for `foo` one must use `myapp help foo`. With this change
`myapp foo --help` will produce the same output as `myapp help foo` by
transforming the --help request into a help subcommand one. This is only done
when there are any options on the command line other than --help. When a top
level --help is requested the original behavior of print_help_if_requested()
is preserved.

Change-Id: I628bbfc383de516045288512cc023213d723a027
Closes-Bug: 1444983
"}]
commit_message:
Allow subcommands to accept --help when using 'deferred_help'.

This patch changes how cliff handles help for subcommands but only when
'deferred_help' is enabled. Currently cliff consumes --help requests at the top
level. This means `myapp foo --help` and `myapp --help` produce the same output.
To get help for `foo` one must use `myapp help foo`. With this change
`myapp foo --help` will produce the same output as `myapp help foo` by
transforming the --help request into a help subcommand one. This is only done
when there are any options on the command line other than --help. When a top
level --help is requested the original behavior of print_help_if_requested()
is preserved.

Change-Id: I628bbfc383de516045288512cc023213d723a027
Closes-Bug: 1444983

commit_message:
Modal service is incorrectly named

Currently, the simple modal service is named "modal.service.js". This is
incorrect, the file name should be "simple-modal.service.js".
Also fixed linting issues.

Why do we care about a rename?
Leaving it as is leaves room for naming collision.
We will likely introduce other modal services in the near future
(for example, the wizard-modal.service)

Change-Id: I61b9c93f37adf0004e99970cf9194ba4fd22eb00
Closes-Bug: #1475046

commit_message:
Validate maximum limit for quota

Currently, when updating quota using limit larger than 2**31 -1,
there will be a DBError. The maximum limit needs to be validated.
And the maximum value is defined by SQL integer type INT, which
is a general value:
http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/integer-types.html
http://www.postgresql.org/docs/9.1/static/datatype-numeric.html

Change-Id: Idf890c57342378d0a71f6b18eb42425d463b13ef
Closes-bug: #1433052

commit_message:
Periodically checks the status of nodes in DEPLOYING state

Periodically checks the nodes in DEPLOYING and the state of the conductor
deploying them. If we find out that a conductor that was provisioning
the node has died we then break release the node and gracefully mark
the deployment as failed.

A new method called "get_offline_conductors" was added to the database
api which return a list of conductor hostnames that are offline.

Closes-Bug: #1461937
Change-Id: I293d3ff18e949b305e6404b8d3ceb75e29b88356

commit_message:
[UI changes] Added ability to create raid of UI

- Added a new tab Storage, which shows the status of all
controllers on all nodes of our environment. For each
controller, we can view all created virtual disks (raid),
all created caches, global hot spare and unused drives.
As well as state of all members of these disk groups.

- On the disk configuration added sub tabs. When
selecting a node that has a raid controller, on this
page we can go to the tab controller. Where we can see
the virtual drives, if they are created, and unused
drives. For unused disks available opportunity to select
a number of drives and convert them to a new virtual
drive. In this type and their amount depends on which of
them we can create.

- Added new dialogs: create virtual drives and warning
about possible data loss when you press reset, revert
changes and load defaults on the configuration page raid
controllers.

Change-Id: I6901f14f67c51d29e69adac03ed9d929fe0ca828

commit_message:
Cache the MultiFernet instance

This prevents keystone from hitting the disk on every request where it
needs to use Fernet keys (every authenticated request, every token
create request, etc).

Closes-Bug: 1452418

commit_message:
Basic plugins implementation (Ceph in core)

Related to blueprint nailgun-plugins

This is the same basic implementation of plugins
as was first created for Ceph as a plugin, but
without moving Ceph from the core. This is a
base for us in order to build YAML-based plugins
in 6.0 and any other plugins further.

Change-Id: I1560268db10b46a4367229351fc728cc95118280

commit_message:
Added ironic puppet module.

As far as we are moving toward closer openstack integration
as a first step we are planning to use ironic as our
provisioning tool. For the start we are planning to
avoid using ISCSI, glance, neutron so we need just ironic
and keystone installed on master node.
Puppet module which is able to deploy ironic from
source git repository. The work is in progress.
Will be improved in the future. For details look at
https://blueprints.launchpad.net/fuel/+spec/provision-ironic-puppet

Change-Id: I7ab5746be3ba773d623d925368bfecd0845575b6

commit_message:
bump keystonemiddleware to g-r compatible version

The current minimum of keystonemiddleware has a pbr requirement of
pbr (>=0.6,!=0.7,<1.0) this forces a downgrade of pbr to 0.11 which
is incompatible with the current requirements and syntax of
global-requirements. Version 2.0.0 of keystonemiddleware has a pbr
requirement of pbr (>=0.11,<2.0) which will not force a downgrade of
pbr.

Change-Id: I5c7f8bc6fcb495e6866d8405effbff78ff0179c3

commit_message:
Move mysql datadir to a sub-directory on mounted volume

Having the mysql datadir located at root of a mounted volume
(which happens with volume support enabled) causes problems for
backup/restore and resize. Mysql decides that the "lost+found"
directory, which the operating system puts at the root of each
file system, is actually a mysql "database".

This change causes the guest agent to move the datadir into a
sub-directory called "data" on the mounted volume.

Change-Id: Ica628012a5708374d73e5394e370da2514300939
Co-Authored-By: Simon Chang <schang@tesora.com>
Closes-bug: 1370646

subject: objects: fix deserialization with nested backleveling
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-07-16 13:38:13.000000000', 'files': ['nova/objects/base.py', 'nova/tests/unit/objects/test_objects.py'], 'message': "objects: fix deserialization with nested backleveling

If a top-level object can be serialized but one of the nested objects
throws an IncompatibleObjectVersion what happens, due to the way that we
handle all exceptions from the recursion at the top level is that
conductor gets asked to backport the top-level object to the nested
object's latest known version - this is completely wrong.

This patch moves the handling of the exception inside the
obj_from_primitive method, so that every level of recursion can ask the
conductor for backleveling if necessary.

Closes-bug: 1475254
Closes-bug: 1275675
(cherry picked from commit 3d93478b106a47ddbd02546d385cc90578c92fb7)

Conflicts:
	nova/tests/unit/objects/test_objects.py

Change-Id: I24d7123e832a99410601df5bb2cc3756763671a6
"}]
commit_message:
objects: fix deserialization with nested backleveling

If a top-level object can be serialized but one of the nested objects
throws an IncompatibleObjectVersion what happens, due to the way that we
handle all exceptions from the recursion at the top level is that
conductor gets asked to backport the top-level object to the nested
object's latest known version - this is completely wrong.

This patch moves the handling of the exception inside the
obj_from_primitive method, so that every level of recursion can ask the
conductor for backleveling if necessary.

Closes-bug: 1475254
Closes-bug: 1275675
(cherry picked from commit 3d93478b106a47ddbd02546d385cc90578c92fb7)

Conflicts:
	nova/tests/unit/objects/test_objects.py

Change-Id: I24d7123e832a99410601df5bb2cc3756763671a6

commit_message:
Adds a small update to tagging guidance

To cover an edge-case discussed in Ic1b2ecf9459798b14db12d449e003648c4228550
A tag query may appear to be self-contradictory, but this should
be treated as a valid query and will most likely just return an
empty result set.

Change-Id: I546d8b9b80d4ba536494051b9a02013c6813d723

commit_message:
Cells: add instance cell registration utility to nova-manage

The patch enables an admin to register instances within a cell.
This is done via:

  nova-manage cell_v2 register_instances

With the following parameters:
     --cell_uuid - mandatory - the cell uuid
     --limit - optional - the maximum number of mappings to be done
                          in this iteration
     --marker - optional - this should be used if the previous run
                           had a limit parameter
     --verbose - optional - prints out useful debug information

NOTE: each time the utility is run it will print the marker that
should be used for the next iteration.

DocImpact

Implements blueprint cells-instance-migration

Change-Id: Ic03fda8bbd0b8d07e61fc08f240750c17c3ef28a

Changeset ed9f1b8b restricted the allowed options for iscsi_iface
to the allowed transports mentioned in the help text. iface &
transport are distinct entities for open-iscsi, and an iface is
generally a mix of transport plus an underlying interface, hence
this change was incorrect. This breaks transport support and is
generally incorrect, hence reverting

Closes-Bug:1466730
Change-Id: I687fb9c95133dbbb193004df44794404b58ca692
'}]
commit_message:
libvirt : remove broken olso_config choices option

Changeset ed9f1b8b restricted the allowed options for iscsi_iface
to the allowed transports mentioned in the help text. iface &
transport are distinct entities for open-iscsi, and an iface is
generally a mix of transport plus an underlying interface, hence
this change was incorrect. This breaks transport support and is
generally incorrect, hence reverting

Closes-Bug:1466730
Change-Id: I687fb9c95133dbbb193004df44794404b58ca692

[{'number': 21, 'created': '2015-07-09 06:18:38.000000000', 'files': ['keystonemiddleware/tests/unit/auth_token/test_auth_token_middleware.py', 'keystonemiddleware/auth_token/__init__.py'], 'message': 'Send the correct user-agent to Keystone

The identity server access log should be able to log which user-agent
made the request using the following string format:
    "{project}/{project_version}
     keystonemiddleware.auth_token/{keystonemiddleware_version}"

This format is documented in rfc7231:
https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-5.5.3

The {project} value will be retrieved from the oslo_config configuration
option/attribute named 'project' or from a 'project' paste.deploy option
for services that don't use oslo_config (e.g. Swift). If neither is
found then we will only log
"keystonemiddleware.auth_token/{keystonemiddleware_version}".

Co-Authored-By: David Stanek <dstanek@dstanek.com>
Closes-Bug: #1450666
Change-Id: Ic87861d2f9fefb3fe78cc93adc73acad9a837b39
'}]
commit_message:
Send the correct user-agent to Keystone

The identity server access log should be able to log which user-agent
made the request using the following string format:
    "{project}/{project_version}
     keystonemiddleware.auth_token/{keystonemiddleware_version}"

This format is documented in rfc7231:
https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-5.5.3

The {project} value will be retrieved from the oslo_config configuration
option/attribute named 'project' or from a 'project' paste.deploy option
for services that don't use oslo_config (e.g. Swift). If neither is
found then we will only log
"keystonemiddleware.auth_token/{keystonemiddleware_version}".

Co-Authored-By: David Stanek <dstanek@dstanek.com>
Closes-Bug: #1450666
Change-Id: Ic87861d2f9fefb3fe78cc93adc73acad9a837b39

commit_message:
Jumbo frames between instances

Employ jumbo frames between instances using
mtu-selection-and-advertisement neutron feature.
Instances will receive DHCP and RA MTU options when
the network's preferred MTU is known.

Upstream project: openstack/puppet-neutron
Upstream review: https://review.openstack.org/199999/
Implements: blueprint jumbo-frames-between-instances
Change-Id: I37212f7e59f2b738f3d7a38cbed6279c4dea965b

commit_message:
DO NOT MERGE: RBAC PATCH WITH SPLIT MIGRATIONS

Network RBAC DB setup and legacy migration

This patch implements the database model required for the network
RBAC work. In addition it migrates the current network and subnet
'shared' attributes to leverage the new table.

'shared' is no longer a property of the DB model because its status
is based on the tenant ID of the API caller. From an API perspective
this is the same (tenants will see networks as 'shared=True' if the
network is shared with them). However, internal callers (e.g. plugins,
drivers, services) will not be able to check for the 'shared' attribute
on network and subnet db objects any more.

This patch just achieves parity with the current shared behavior so it
doesn't add the ability to manipulate the RBAC entries directly. The
RBAC API is in the following patch.

Change-Id: I68a967c3cf447b9128ed63175df63e80bb516cd0
Partially-Implements: blueprint rbac-networks

commit_message:
Allow int tests to run in SSL environment

- int tests would raise an SSLError because
we had no way to set the cacert when creating the
nova client.
- Added "cacert" parameter on the integration test
config file.
- Setting the cacert parameter on nova_client.Client
constructor in create_nova_client method.
- Defaulting cacert to None if none specified.

Change-Id: Ia16bc9d52ba146d92b165e6ee046062a90f7b10c
Closes-Bug: #1474503

commit_message:
Scenario test for vpnaas: ipsec-site-connection

The test verifies that it is possible to establish a vpn
connection between two sites. And then it performs basic
connectivity test. It pings IP address of site2 from an
IP address of site1.
The patchset implements scenario test for both
openswan and strongswan device drivers.

Change-Id: I5ff943d4cb4de06c79c2f2d0fee178ad992f36d1

commit_message:
VPNaaS DevStack Plugin support

Adding plugin support for the neutron-vpnaas repo. Later, will
remove the setup from the DevStack repo.

One note: Since the VPN agent is a subclass of the L3 agent,
which in turn is a subclass of the FW agent, the startup for
the VPN agent process must check to see if the FW service is
enabled, and if so, include that configuration file (AFAICT).

Change-Id: I6c32165a544223ccf02228c953766b5211426ed0
Partial-Bug: 1473475

commit_message:
Fixing up random to be less noisy

This just targets specific functions within random, rather than
the module itself. We use the blacklist calls stuff for this so
there is now no need for a special plugin.

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-07-15 09:29:59.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/openvswitch/agent/ovs_neutron_agent.py'], 'message': 'Avoid using logging in signal handler

In some cases, logging can grab locks and thusly attempt to reschedule,
which will fail in signal handlers. this patch removes the actions
from the signal handers, just set a flat if it got a signal, then in
rpc_loop, check the flag and perform appropriate actions.

Change-Id: I7a477e1c95b63fa8070ec9d08656156571421bb6
Partial-Bug: #1029727
'}]
commit_message:
Avoid using logging in signal handler

In some cases, logging can grab locks and thusly attempt to reschedule,
which will fail in signal handlers. this patch removes the actions
from the signal handers, just set a flat if it got a signal, then in
rpc_loop, check the flag and perform appropriate actions.

Change-Id: I7a477e1c95b63fa8070ec9d08656156571421bb6
Partial-Bug: #1029727

from environment variable MIRROR_CENTOS for all new environments.

commit_message:
Switch from deprecated isotime

oslo_utils.timeutils.isotime() is deprecated as of 1.6 so we need
to stop using it.

The deprecation message says to use datetime.datetime.isoformat()
instead, but the format of the string generated by isoformat isn't
the same as the format of the string generated by isotime. The string
is used in tokens and other public APIs and we can't change it
without potentially breaking clients.

So the workaround is to copy the current implementation from
oslo_utils.timeutils.isotime() to keystone.common.utils.isotime().

Change-Id: I34b12b96de3ea21beaf935ed8a9f6bae2fe0d0bc
Closes-Bug: 1461251

commit_message:
Make predefined_networks parameter optional

Only create predefined networks in Neutron if 'predefined_network' attribute in
clster settings is present and not empty. Otherwise, skip this part of manifest.

So, if you need to skip creation of predefined networks, delete this parameter
or leave it empty in deployment settings.

It is important to note that if user disabled creation of predefined networks,
some components that depend on them might fail to install. The list
(non-comprehensive) includes:

* Murano
* Sahara
* Mellanox plugin for Neutron

Other services might be impacted as well.

Change-Id: Iceed16072628cced6de9f8704b35f21fd4342e87
Closes-bug: 1471244
DocImpact
